N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 15 ยง 91.8 - Printers' reports for uniform traffic ticket

State Regulations

Each printer who supplies uniform traffic tickets to any
enforcement agency shall make a report thereof to the commissioner at Albany, New York, within five days after shipment supplying the following
information: (a) name and address of
enforcement agency; (b) first and
last serial numbers of packets; (c) serial number of any missing packets; (d) a statement as to the size and face of
type used in printing the warning required to appear in red on part
I; (e) date of shipment or
delivery. Notes
